                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12431983" author="djd" created="Thu, 31 Aug 2006 22:10:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Change the derby_tests.policy file to use specific properties for the testing jar and the client jar to allow them to be in different locations to the remaining derby code. Have the harness set these properties when running with a security manager using the values determined by the JUnit test utility SecurityManagerSetup. SecurityManagerSetup already set up different properties based upon anticipated need.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running derbyall with these changes now. May not be ready for commit since I just remembered there are other policy files, though I&apos;m not sure how many are really used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12435803" author="rhillegas" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2006 15:31:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 10.2.2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12435911" author="djd" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2006 16:53:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Already fixed in 10.3, &amp;amp; merged to 10.2.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12440284" author="djd" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2006 00:12:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;See about 50 test failures running the tests using the layout in the 10.2.1.6 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12447476" author="djd" created="Mon, 6 Nov 2006 17:10:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tested with trunk jars from svn 470416 separating derbytesting.jar into separate directory called test at same level as lib.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12458319" author="djd" created="Thu, 14 Dec 2006 00:43:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;need to edit fix in versions&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12458320" author="djd" created="Thu, 14 Dec 2006 00:44:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only fixed in trunk.&lt;br/&gt;
Running the tests in 10.2.2.0 from the release candidate still shows 50+ tests failing when running without changing the release layout.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12458321" author="djd" created="Thu, 14 Dec 2006 00:45:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing after updating the affects/fix in to reflect reality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
